Title: systemd: enable indefinite service restarts
Description:
When a service fails to start up enough times in a row, systemd gives up on it.
On servers, this isn’t what I want — in general it’s helpful for automated recovery if daemons are restarted indefinitely. As long as you don’t have circular dependencies between services, all your services will eventually come up after transient failures, without having to specify dependencies.

Title: RSA is deceptively simple (and fun)
Description:
While reading Real-World Cryptography, I came across the "million message attack".
This is an attack that Daniel Bleichenbacher demonstrated in 1998, which effectively broke RSA with a particular encoding function called PKCS #1.
It was only mentioned briefly, so I dug in and decided to try to understand the attack, eventually to implement it.
